1
00:00:01,193 --> 00:00:03,505
Hahahaha...

2
00:00:03,588 --> 00:00:05,592
Fufufufu... Fuhahaha...

3
00:00:06,051 --> 00:00:09,057
Fuhahaha... As expected of the great detective.

4
00:00:09,600 --> 00:00:11,186
To have seen through
this Kaito K's hideout...

5
00:00:11,269 --> 00:00:12,648
How impressive.

6
00:00:13,023 --> 00:00:15,737
So you've finally shown yourself,
Kaito K.

7
00:00:15,821 --> 00:00:18,701
Master, it's dangerous.

8
00:00:18,785 --> 00:00:19,995
Please come down.

9
00:00:20,246 --> 00:00:24,964
Silence, Sada.
I am not the master... I am Kaito K.

10
00:00:25,047 --> 00:00:26,216
Master...

11
00:00:26,551 --> 00:00:27,761
Umm...

12
00:00:27,845 --> 00:00:31,727
We were invited to dinner
by that person, right?

13
00:00:31,811 --> 00:00:33,355
What's going on?

14
00:00:33,639 --> 00:00:35,392
You didn't know?

15
00:00:36,561 --> 00:00:39,108
My old man is an obsessive detective fan.

16
00:00:39,943 --> 00:00:41,237
And among them all...

17
00:00:41,321 --> 00:00:43,075
Mouri-san is his absolute favorite.

18
00:00:43,325 --> 00:00:44,787
Oh really...

19
00:00:44,870 --> 00:00:48,001
Now that you mention it, there was a statue
of the old man earlier.

20
00:00:48,085 --> 00:00:49,504
So cool...

21
00:00:49,963 --> 00:00:53,428
So sometimes he challenges him to a match
like that.

22
00:00:53,679 --> 00:00:54,138
Pretending to be Kaito K himself.

23
00:00:54,138 --> 00:00:56,518
Get down here,
you bastard!

24
00:00:56,602 --> 00:00:59,691
Haha... What a peculiar hobby.

25
00:01:00,317 --> 00:01:02,279
Honestly...
Oh!

26
00:01:04,242 --> 00:01:07,331
Men really are
such foolish creatures, aren't they?

27
00:01:08,291 --> 00:01:10,797
The time limit is 30 minutes.

28
00:01:11,256 --> 00:01:13,845
Try to catch me, everyone.

29
00:01:13,928 --> 00:01:18,395
If you manage to catch me
before that grand clock strikes six...

30
00:01:18,478 --> 00:01:21,067
I shall present you with a marvelous prize.

31
00:01:21,359 --> 00:01:25,534
Well then, I wish you luck.
Fuh... Hahahaha...

32
00:01:25,752 --> 00:01:31,764
♪~

33
00:01:38,736 --> 00:01:42,494
The darkness of shadows and the depth of night...
The light of deduction cuts right through.

34
00:01:42,577 --> 00:01:46,419
A vast estate filled with tricks...
The shocking reason Kogoro was targeted.

35
00:01:46,502 --> 00:01:47,963
Seeing through the one and only truth...

36
00:01:48,046 --> 00:01:49,883
A child's appearance, an adult's mind...
 
37
00:01:49,967 --> 00:01:52,681
His name is Detective Conan!

38
00:03:14,470 --> 00:03:20,482
~♪

39
00:03:24,396 --> 00:03:30,196
"The Secret of the Kogoro Mouri Statue"

40
00:03:34,278 --> 00:03:37,158
Still... this garden is incredible as always.

41
00:03:37,242 --> 00:03:40,081
It really is like there's a whole town
inside the garden.

42
00:03:40,164 --> 00:03:43,380
We actually call it the "Town" rather than a garden.

43
00:03:43,755 --> 00:03:46,928
Haha... So it's perfect for a game of tag, huh?

44
00:03:49,684 --> 00:03:52,773
Got him... That should be a dead end.

45
00:03:55,446 --> 00:03:57,950
Huh? Ah!
Ah!

46
00:03:59,202 --> 00:04:01,165
Kataoka-san disappeared?

47
00:04:01,416 --> 00:04:04,087
No way... Huh?

48
00:04:10,642 --> 00:04:11,978
Hmm...
Huh?

49
00:04:12,396 --> 00:04:13,857
This is...

50
00:04:14,692 --> 00:04:15,694
Hmph.

51
00:04:16,236 --> 00:04:18,992
Oh... Did you figure something out, Conan-kun?

52
00:04:19,075 --> 00:04:22,248
Don't you think it's weird? This clock...

53
00:04:22,958 --> 00:04:25,254
It's hung way too low, for one...

54
00:04:25,339 --> 00:04:28,720
And both the hour and minute hands
pointing at six at the same time...

55
00:04:28,803 --> 00:04:30,139
That's strange, right?

56
00:04:30,223 --> 00:04:31,225
Now that you mention it...

57
00:04:31,309 --> 00:04:34,231
Ah... Could it be...

58
00:04:36,068 --> 00:04:37,363
Ah... Yeah.

59
00:04:38,406 --> 00:04:42,121
(electronic sound)
Whoa, whoa whoa...

60
00:04:43,207 --> 00:04:45,879
That's right. This is the entrance to the underground passage.

61
00:04:45,963 --> 00:04:48,385
Ouch...

62
00:04:49,595 --> 00:04:51,766
Whoa! Kaito K!

63
00:04:51,849 --> 00:04:55,649
Fufufu... Hahahaha...
Wait... Whoa!

64
00:04:55,732 --> 00:04:57,026
Ah! Sorry, Dad!

65
00:04:57,110 --> 00:04:59,657
I'll circle around to the exit.

66
00:04:59,740 --> 00:05:02,161
We'll catch him in a pincer attack.
Right.

67
00:05:11,723 --> 00:05:13,393
Ah... This is...

68
00:05:13,935 --> 00:05:16,816
The footprints in the mud are still fresh.

69
00:05:16,899 --> 00:05:18,945
No doubt, he went this way.
Yeah.

70
00:05:23,162 --> 00:05:24,332
Ran-neechan, over there.

71
00:05:24,415 --> 00:05:25,584
Found him.

72
00:05:27,963 --> 00:05:28,965
Whoa!

73
00:05:30,344 --> 00:05:32,055
Master, prepare yourself.

74
00:05:32,138 --> 00:05:33,433
Whoa...

75
00:05:34,977 --> 00:05:36,522
Whoa!
Ahh!

76
00:05:37,231 --> 00:05:39,528
My apologies... How clumsy of me...

77
00:05:39,862 --> 00:05:41,324
Then hurry up and get off!

78
00:05:41,574 --> 00:05:43,495
P-Please excuse me.

79
00:05:46,959 --> 00:05:48,588
Huh? If we go this way...

80
00:05:48,672 --> 00:05:52,763
Yes, it leads to the front
of the main house, the starting point.

81
00:05:58,900 --> 00:06:00,987
It seems he's heading for the back garden.

82
00:06:01,280 --> 00:06:03,660
You two, go around from that side.

83
00:06:04,119 --> 00:06:05,831
This time we'll really trap him.

84
00:06:05,914 --> 00:06:07,501
Understood.

85
00:06:13,888 --> 00:06:16,519
Dammit... This mansion is way too huge.

86
00:06:16,602 --> 00:06:19,107
He went that way! Catch him!

87
00:06:20,986 --> 00:06:22,364
Ah!

88
00:06:23,908 --> 00:06:25,244
Whoa!

89
00:06:25,328 --> 00:06:27,708
Huh?
Conan-kun, let's go!

90
00:06:27,791 --> 00:06:29,169
Right...

91
00:06:30,212 --> 00:06:31,256
Hmph.

92
00:06:32,551 --> 00:06:33,970
(cat meows)
Look out!

93
00:06:34,137 --> 00:06:35,974
(brakes screech)

94
00:06:42,028 --> 00:06:44,408
Using a bicycle... Isn't that cheating?

95
00:06:44,492 --> 00:06:45,494
Well, yeah.

96
00:06:51,756 --> 00:06:54,345
This is just like a maze.

97
00:06:54,887 --> 00:06:57,309
At this rate, we'll have no idea where he went...
(collision sound)

98
00:06:57,392 --> 00:06:59,271
Ahh!
This way!

99
00:07:04,448 --> 00:07:05,492
Ah!

100
00:07:05,575 --> 00:07:07,496
Ouch...

101
00:07:07,579 --> 00:07:09,123
Are you alright?

102
00:07:09,207 --> 00:07:11,462
Yes... We just ran into each other...

103
00:07:11,546 --> 00:07:13,925
I was startled and simply tripped.

104
00:07:14,301 --> 00:07:15,428
What about Kataoka-san?

105
00:07:15,846 --> 00:07:18,560
Most likely headed toward the main house.

106
00:07:18,893 --> 00:07:20,104
Seven minutes left.

107
00:07:20,187 --> 00:07:22,985
Uwaah!
(falling sound)

108
00:07:24,488 --> 00:07:25,532
Yurie-san.

109
00:07:26,157 --> 00:07:27,494
Did you hear that? That voice just now...

110
00:07:27,578 --> 00:07:29,915
Yes... What happened?

111
00:07:29,999 --> 00:07:32,086
I just got here myself, so...

112
00:07:32,169 --> 00:07:36,846
Don't tell me something's happened to the master...
Master!

113
00:07:41,772 --> 00:07:43,860
Ran-neechan, what about over there?

114
00:07:43,943 --> 00:07:46,324
No, nobody here either.

115
00:07:46,616 --> 00:07:49,580
Dammit... Where on earth is he?

116
00:07:50,080 --> 00:07:51,417
What's wrong?
Ah...

117
00:07:51,500 --> 00:07:53,338
I heard a pretty loud voice.

118
00:07:53,755 --> 00:07:55,717
Seiya-san, where were you all this time...

119
00:07:56,134 --> 00:07:59,223
Where? I was in my room listening to music...

120
00:07:59,975 --> 00:08:02,397
Ahh! Master!
Huh?

121
00:08:02,481 --> 00:08:05,654
Sada? It came from the back garden...

122
00:08:06,781 --> 00:08:07,991
Ah!

123
00:08:08,200 --> 00:08:10,330
Master, please... Hold on...

124
00:08:11,081 --> 00:08:12,334
Master!

125
00:08:13,336 --> 00:08:15,882
What happened? Did something happen?

126
00:08:16,842 --> 00:08:18,220
W-Well...

127
00:08:25,986 --> 00:08:27,572
Move.
Whoa!

128
00:08:28,950 --> 00:08:31,121
It's no use... He's dead.

129
00:08:46,097 --> 00:08:48,310
The deceased is the master of this house...

130
00:08:48,394 --> 00:08:52,234
Financier Kataoka Eisuke-san, 54 years old.

131
00:08:52,318 --> 00:08:54,823
He suffered severe impact to the back of his body.

132
00:08:55,283 --> 00:08:58,246
In particular, the damage to the back of the head is extensive...

133
00:08:58,330 --> 00:09:00,208
And that appears to be the fatal injury.

134
00:09:00,626 --> 00:09:04,634
The time of death is without a doubt 5:55 PM.

135
00:09:04,718 --> 00:09:06,472
Everyone present here, at that moment...

136
00:09:06,805 --> 00:09:11,022
Heard Kataoka-san's scream
and the sound of a ladder falling.

137
00:09:11,482 --> 00:09:15,615
I hear Kataoka-san was in the middle of a game
with you all.

138
00:09:15,698 --> 00:09:19,831
Yeah, we were playing tag.
We were "it."

139
00:09:19,915 --> 00:09:23,171
Good grief... At his age,
what was he doing?

140
00:09:23,254 --> 00:09:24,716
Well...

141
00:09:25,843 --> 00:09:27,096
Ah...

142
00:09:28,557 --> 00:09:30,143
So it really was an accident?

143
00:09:30,603 --> 00:09:32,649
Hmm... Well, on the ladder...

144
00:09:32,732 --> 00:09:35,905
Kataoka-san's shoe prints were found, after all.

145
00:09:36,155 --> 00:09:39,329
Most likely, Kataoka-san was climbing the ladder...

146
00:09:39,412 --> 00:09:41,917
He lost his balance and fell.

147
00:09:42,961 --> 00:09:45,299
I believe it's safe to assume that.

148
00:09:45,383 --> 00:09:46,760
The bruise on the victim's cheek...

149
00:09:47,052 --> 00:09:50,560
Was probably caused when he fell from the ladder as well.

150
00:09:51,436 --> 00:09:53,399
He got what he deserved.

151
00:09:53,482 --> 00:09:56,530
Getting so wrapped up in such childish games
all the time...

152
00:09:56,613 --> 00:09:59,076
Hmm?
She's Kataoka-san's wife.

153
00:09:59,160 --> 00:10:02,625
After his first wife passed away,
he remarried three years ago.

154
00:10:02,709 --> 00:10:03,711
Hmm.

155
00:10:06,007 --> 00:10:09,306
Huh? Yurie-san, you're not wearing
a wedding ring?

156
00:10:09,389 --> 00:10:12,478
It's a bother, so I've just been
leaving it off.

157
00:10:13,314 --> 00:10:16,194
But in that case, that ring mark...

158
00:10:18,490 --> 00:10:20,870
...So, the son from the first wife is him?

159
00:10:20,953 --> 00:10:23,709
Yes. When his mother passed away...

160
00:10:23,792 --> 00:10:28,092
He seemed to resent Kataoka-san,
blaming his reckless father for it.

161
00:10:28,552 --> 00:10:30,848
Well, it's a fitting way for my old man to die.

162
00:10:30,932 --> 00:10:32,100
Huh...

163
00:10:32,560 --> 00:10:35,483
Hey, Seiya-san... What happened to your hand?

164
00:10:35,816 --> 00:10:40,242
Huh? Oh, just... my guitar string, a little earlier.

165
00:10:41,077 --> 00:10:43,540
Huh? Why was this person, back then...

166
00:10:43,624 --> 00:10:46,880
What's wrong?
I heard a pretty loud voice.

167
00:10:47,130 --> 00:10:49,260
Seiya-san, where were you all this time...

168
00:10:49,678 --> 00:10:52,767
Where? I was in my room listening to music...

169
00:10:53,894 --> 00:10:56,817
I have caused everyone
a great deal of trouble...

170
00:10:56,900 --> 00:10:59,238
I am terribly sorry.

171
00:10:59,322 --> 00:11:01,910
But... was it truly an accident?

172
00:11:01,994 --> 00:11:02,996
Huh?

173
00:11:03,079 --> 00:11:06,420
Is there something on your mind,
Mouri-kun?

174
00:11:07,129 --> 00:11:09,759
Whenever Kataoka-san faced me in a match...

175
00:11:09,843 --> 00:11:12,682
He always set up some kind of trick.

176
00:11:12,765 --> 00:11:16,105
But this time, he just ran and ran.

177
00:11:16,440 --> 00:11:18,444
Aren't you overthinking it?

178
00:11:18,527 --> 00:11:21,533
He's an amateur. Sometimes that's just how it goes.

179
00:11:21,616 --> 00:11:24,873
Yeah... Well, I suppose you might be right.

180
00:11:24,956 --> 00:11:26,793
Then it's settled as an accidental death.

181
00:11:26,877 --> 00:11:28,464
Yes, I suppose so.

182
00:11:28,839 --> 00:11:31,553
No... The old man is right.

183
00:11:31,636 --> 00:11:34,058
For an accident, there are several
strange points.

184
00:11:34,684 --> 00:11:37,565
First, the body wasn't sweating.

185
00:11:37,940 --> 00:11:40,863
Even though he should've been running
right up until he died.

186
00:11:41,782 --> 00:11:43,827
And also... Ah!

187
00:11:47,209 --> 00:11:50,716
Ha... Don't tell me... It was here?

188
00:11:55,476 --> 00:11:57,814
In that case, it must be over there.

189
00:12:01,571 --> 00:12:03,992
It should be somewhere
around here...

190
00:12:08,293 --> 00:12:10,381
As I thought, this one too... Huh?

191
00:12:10,756 --> 00:12:12,092
Whoa!

192
00:12:12,468 --> 00:12:15,933
What do you mean "Whoa"?
Like I'm some kind of monster.

193
00:12:16,016 --> 00:12:18,647
I've been searching for you, shouting my head off.

194
00:12:18,730 --> 00:12:21,278
Huh? Then why, back then...
(piano playing)

195
00:12:21,278 --> 00:12:21,695
(piano playing)

196
00:12:21,695 --> 00:12:22,697
(piano playing)
Huh?

197
00:12:22,697 --> 00:12:23,072
(piano playing)

198
00:12:23,072 --> 00:12:24,742
(piano playing)
It's a piece that the late
Kataoka-san was fond of.

199
00:12:24,742 --> 00:12:25,953
It's a piece that the late
Kataoka-san was fond of.

200
00:12:26,663 --> 00:12:30,963
Someone in the main house must be playing it.
In his memory.

201
00:12:31,423 --> 00:12:34,178
Old man, try moving this statue.

202
00:12:34,261 --> 00:12:37,727
Huh? It's a bronze statue.
No way it's gonna move.

203
00:12:37,810 --> 00:12:40,774
But don't you think something's
weird about this statue?

204
00:12:40,858 --> 00:12:42,110
Huh?

205
00:12:42,403 --> 00:12:43,989
The mustache that shouldn't be connected...

206
00:12:44,072 --> 00:12:46,620
Your mustache... is connected.

207
00:12:46,703 --> 00:12:48,749
Almost like it's a fake.

208
00:12:48,832 --> 00:12:49,834
Oh!

209
00:12:51,671 --> 00:12:53,592
Oww...
This one?

210
00:12:55,888 --> 00:12:58,602
What? There's nothing here.

211
00:12:58,685 --> 00:13:03,445
(cat meows and clattering sounds)

212
00:13:03,946 --> 00:13:05,324
That sound...

213
00:13:05,991 --> 00:13:08,079
I see...
Huh?

214
00:13:10,543 --> 00:13:11,795
Let me borrow this.

215
00:13:11,878 --> 00:13:14,132
(cat meows and clattering sounds)

216
00:13:14,509 --> 00:13:17,974
I see... So that's what it was.

217
00:13:18,057 --> 00:13:19,059
Oh?
Huh?

218
00:13:19,561 --> 00:13:22,400
What are you doing in a place like this,
Conan-kun?

219
00:13:22,483 --> 00:13:24,320
Ah, Takagi-keiji.

220
00:13:24,404 --> 00:13:26,908
The old man Mouri asked me to do something...

221
00:13:26,992 --> 00:13:30,123
Huh? But Mouri-san is right over there...

222
00:13:30,206 --> 00:13:31,376
Never mind, never mind.

223
00:13:31,459 --> 00:13:32,670
Huh?

224
00:13:33,630 --> 00:13:37,722
Old man, I brought everyone,
just like you asked.

225
00:13:37,805 --> 00:13:41,228
What on earth is this about, Mouri-kun?

226
00:13:41,313 --> 00:13:42,982
I've finally figured it out.

227
00:13:43,275 --> 00:13:47,240
The truth behind this murder
disguised as an accident.

228
00:13:47,658 --> 00:13:48,869
What?!

229
00:13:48,952 --> 00:13:53,252
But the scene's circumstances
can only be seen as an accident.

230
00:13:53,337 --> 00:13:55,256
Why do you believe it's murder?

231
00:13:55,716 --> 00:13:56,760
The bruise.

232
00:13:56,843 --> 00:14:00,141
The bruise... You mean the one
on the victim's cheek?

233
00:14:00,224 --> 00:14:02,938
That was likely caused when he fell
from the ladder.

234
00:14:03,398 --> 00:14:05,694
I thought so too, at first.

235
00:14:05,778 --> 00:14:09,201
But this statue
told me otherwise.

236
00:14:09,494 --> 00:14:13,084
Take a close look...
The nose is chipped, isn't it?

237
00:14:13,335 --> 00:14:15,798
It certainly is... but...

238
00:14:15,881 --> 00:14:17,677
It's a very fresh wound.

239
00:14:17,760 --> 00:14:22,227
As if something struck it
with great force just moments ago.

240
00:14:22,311 --> 00:14:23,563
No way...

241
00:14:23,647 --> 00:14:26,653
Yes. If you examine the marks,
they should match.

242
00:14:27,279 --> 00:14:28,949
The bruise on the victim's cheek...

243
00:14:29,032 --> 00:14:31,871
Was caused by colliding
with that nose.

244
00:14:32,205 --> 00:14:34,544
However, the body was found...

245
00:14:34,627 --> 00:14:39,303
Yes. If Kataoka-san had truly
fallen from the ladder...

246
00:14:39,387 --> 00:14:42,643
There's no way he could have struck this statue
so far away.

247
00:14:43,060 --> 00:14:47,319
That's right... Kataoka-san did not
fall from that ladder.

248
00:14:47,778 --> 00:14:51,995
First, he was struck by the culprit here
and knocked unconscious...

249
00:14:52,580 --> 00:14:55,084
Then he was carried
to the spot where he was found...

250
00:14:55,168 --> 00:15:00,011
And murdered by having the back of his head
and his entire body slammed against the stone pavement.

251
00:15:00,679 --> 00:15:04,771
After that, the culprit transferred
Kataoka-san's shoe prints onto the ladder...

252
00:15:04,854 --> 00:15:06,941
Placed that ladder
next to the body...

253
00:15:07,025 --> 00:15:10,699
And made it look as if Kataoka-san
had fallen from it.

254
00:15:12,369 --> 00:15:14,332
Who would do such a thing...

255
00:15:14,415 --> 00:15:17,045
Before that, there's something
I want to confirm.

256
00:15:17,128 --> 00:15:18,423
Takagi-keiji.

257
00:15:19,425 --> 00:15:23,224
Regarding Kataoka-san's cape...
Wasn't the edge torn?

258
00:15:23,308 --> 00:15:24,936
It was not torn.

259
00:15:25,395 --> 00:15:27,608
Don't you find that odd, Ran?

260
00:15:27,691 --> 00:15:29,570
Huh? Ah, that's right...

261
00:15:29,654 --> 00:15:31,407
Hmm? What do you mean?

262
00:15:31,825 --> 00:15:34,956
Kataoka-san's cape
should be torn.

263
00:15:35,039 --> 00:15:37,837
Look out!
(brakes screech)

264
00:15:42,262 --> 00:15:45,602
But the cape on the body
was not torn.

265
00:15:45,686 --> 00:15:47,565
But then why...

266
00:15:47,648 --> 00:15:49,360
The answer is simple.

267
00:15:49,443 --> 00:15:53,493
Because the person you were chasing
was not Kataoka-san.

268
00:15:53,577 --> 00:15:55,037
What?!
What?!

269
00:15:55,414 --> 00:15:58,587
Of course, the Kaito K
we were initially chasing...

270
00:15:58,670 --> 00:15:59,922
Was Kataoka-san.

271
00:16:00,006 --> 00:16:03,053
But partway through,
he was swapped.

272
00:16:03,680 --> 00:16:06,018
Kataoka-san was replaced by the culprit.

273
00:16:06,101 --> 00:16:09,232
Isn't that right, the other Kaito K...

274
00:16:09,317 --> 00:16:12,907
And the one who murdered
Kataoka-san...

275
00:16:12,990 --> 00:16:14,911
Sada Makoto-san.

276
00:16:15,495 --> 00:16:19,337
But Dad... Sada-san was
with us the whole time...

277
00:16:19,420 --> 00:16:21,758
We were chasing Kataoka-san together.

278
00:16:21,841 --> 00:16:23,720
He had no chance to swap...

279
00:16:23,803 --> 00:16:26,684
No, he wasn't with you the whole time.

280
00:16:26,768 --> 00:16:28,980
There was one moment when you were apart.

281
00:16:29,064 --> 00:16:31,193
Right before we came to this back garden.

282
00:16:31,277 --> 00:16:32,363
Ah...

283
00:16:32,738 --> 00:16:35,076
You two, go around from that side.

284
00:16:35,577 --> 00:16:37,163
This time we'll really trap him.

285
00:16:37,246 --> 00:16:38,792
Understood.

286
00:16:38,875 --> 00:16:41,714
Most likely, the original plan
was Kataoka-san's idea.

287
00:16:42,256 --> 00:16:44,762
He had indeed
prepared this swapping trick...

288
00:16:44,845 --> 00:16:46,307
As expected.

289
00:16:46,808 --> 00:16:51,442
But Sada-san's objective
was to use that trick...

290
00:16:51,526 --> 00:16:54,114
To murder Kataoka-san.

291
00:16:54,699 --> 00:16:57,579
After seeing Ran and the others off,
he took a shortcut through the mansion...

292
00:16:58,122 --> 00:17:02,130
He put on the Kaito K costume and mask
he had prepared beforehand...

293
00:17:02,756 --> 00:17:06,096
And attacked the waiting Kataoka-san
from behind, knocking him unconscious...

294
00:17:06,179 --> 00:17:09,895
He hid him behind this statue...

295
00:17:10,480 --> 00:17:13,445
And appeared before Ran and the others
as Kaito K.

296
00:17:13,737 --> 00:17:16,743
So after that, the one we were chasing was...

297
00:17:16,826 --> 00:17:19,874
Not Kataoka-san, but Sada-san.

298
00:17:19,957 --> 00:17:22,045
I checked with the boy earlier...

299
00:17:22,296 --> 00:17:24,425
The bicycle pedals that should have been dirtied
by the Kaito K shoes...

300
00:17:24,508 --> 00:17:27,931
After running through the underground passage...

301
00:17:28,015 --> 00:17:29,351
Were perfectly clean.

302
00:17:30,102 --> 00:17:32,983
And then, with a straight face,
he put on his one-man act...

303
00:17:33,067 --> 00:17:35,739
And Sada-san returned to his original form.

304
00:17:35,822 --> 00:17:38,495
Mouri-san, you're forgetting
something important.

305
00:17:39,079 --> 00:17:42,753
I heard the master's scream
along with Ran-san and the others...

306
00:17:42,836 --> 00:17:45,634
And the sound of the ladder falling.

307
00:17:45,717 --> 00:17:48,556
Would you be referring to this?

308
00:17:49,015 --> 00:17:50,059
Takagi-keiji.

309
00:17:50,142 --> 00:17:51,729
Right.
Hmm?

310
00:17:55,027 --> 00:17:57,741
Uwaah!
(falling sound)

311
00:17:58,200 --> 00:18:01,874
There's no mistake...
It's the same voice and sound from that moment.

312
00:18:02,250 --> 00:18:04,170
It's a stereo recording.

313
00:18:04,964 --> 00:18:06,592
Sada-san had, beforehand...

314
00:18:06,676 --> 00:18:11,435
Recorded Kataoka-san's scream
and the sound of the ladder falling onto a CD.

315
00:18:11,519 --> 00:18:15,819
He set a timer so it would play
at full volume at that exact time.

316
00:18:15,902 --> 00:18:17,531
He had it all set up.

317
00:18:17,906 --> 00:18:20,287
But the truth is, at that moment...

318
00:18:20,370 --> 00:18:23,083
Kataoka-san was still alive.

319
00:18:23,167 --> 00:18:24,920
Right here, behind this statue.

320
00:18:25,505 --> 00:18:28,135
Then... Don't tell me...
While we were inside the mansion...

321
00:18:28,218 --> 00:18:30,348
Searching for Kataoka-san...

322
00:18:30,432 --> 00:18:32,978
Yes. Sada-san came to the back garden...

323
00:18:33,061 --> 00:18:35,358
Killed Kataoka-san...

324
00:18:35,442 --> 00:18:39,533
And in the time before everyone rushed over,
set up the fake scene.

325
00:18:39,617 --> 00:18:41,746
Holding Kataoka-san's body
was also...

326
00:18:41,829 --> 00:18:44,710
To hide the blood spatter
that had gotten on his clothes.

327
00:18:44,793 --> 00:18:45,962
Isn't that right?

328
00:18:47,466 --> 00:18:49,929
Sada-san... Your mistake was...

329
00:18:50,012 --> 00:18:52,851
Turning the stereo volume up too high.

330
00:18:53,143 --> 00:18:57,068
It reached us, far away,
and even reached Seiya-kun...

331
00:18:57,151 --> 00:19:00,283
Who was listening to music with headphones.

332
00:19:00,367 --> 00:19:03,581
Normally, a human voice
would never carry that far.

333
00:19:03,831 --> 00:19:06,587
But... what does any of that prove?

334
00:19:06,671 --> 00:19:08,591
That alone is not evidence.

335
00:19:08,925 --> 00:19:11,806
Indeed. So allow me to show you.

336
00:19:11,889 --> 00:19:15,229
The conclusive proof
that you are the true culprit.

337
00:19:17,651 --> 00:19:20,072
At the crossroads where my statue stands...

338
00:19:20,155 --> 00:19:22,118
After your one-man act...

339
00:19:22,201 --> 00:19:25,542
You must have hidden the disguise items
somewhere around that area.

340
00:19:26,167 --> 00:19:29,800
In fact, there was a hidden compartment
in the statue's pedestal.

341
00:19:29,883 --> 00:19:31,512
But it was empty.

342
00:19:31,929 --> 00:19:33,308
I suppose it was.

343
00:19:33,391 --> 00:19:35,395
Yes. That was merely...

344
00:19:35,478 --> 00:19:39,278
The place to store something
for hiding the disguise items.

345
00:19:40,154 --> 00:19:44,203
At that time, you placed the disguise items
inside the object...

346
00:19:44,288 --> 00:19:46,041
You took out of that hole.

347
00:19:46,124 --> 00:19:47,544
Ah...

348
00:19:48,755 --> 00:19:51,802
(clattering sounds and cat meows)

349
00:19:51,886 --> 00:19:53,806
Ah...

350
00:20:00,362 --> 00:20:02,783
Don't you think this ball is strange?
(clattering sounds)

351
00:20:02,783 --> 00:20:02,866
(clattering sounds)

352
00:20:02,866 --> 00:20:06,374
It's a little too big,
and more than anything, it makes a strange sound.

353
00:20:06,374 --> 00:20:07,292
It's a little too big,
and more than anything, it makes a strange sound.

354
00:20:08,586 --> 00:20:10,673
Hmm.
Ah... Ahh...

355
00:20:11,675 --> 00:20:13,679
Th-This is...

356
00:20:16,435 --> 00:20:20,777
Marble fragments...
It's faint, but there's blood on them.

357
00:20:20,860 --> 00:20:23,031
And white hairs on the wig...

358
00:20:23,115 --> 00:20:26,497
What is the meaning of this,
Sada-san?

359
00:20:28,960 --> 00:20:32,426
At that moment, you took that ball
from the pedestal's hidden compartment...

360
00:20:32,509 --> 00:20:35,348
Hid the disguise items inside it...

361
00:20:35,432 --> 00:20:38,145
And tossed it into Ran and the others' blind spot.

362
00:20:38,813 --> 00:20:42,404
You probably intended
to retrieve it later.

363
00:20:42,696 --> 00:20:44,950
But there were two miscalculations.

364
00:20:45,033 --> 00:20:47,789
One, a stray cat wandered in...

365
00:20:47,873 --> 00:20:50,252
And made the ball go missing.

366
00:20:50,795 --> 00:20:53,718
The other... was that the marble nose fragment
you suddenly had to hide...

367
00:20:53,801 --> 00:20:55,847
The marble nose fragment
you suddenly had to hide...

368
00:20:55,930 --> 00:20:59,271
Made an unnatural sound
inside the ball.

369
00:21:00,482 --> 00:21:03,696
No... I'd say my greatest miscalculation...

370
00:21:03,779 --> 00:21:06,911
Was underestimating your powers of deduction, Mouri-san.

371
00:21:07,161 --> 00:21:08,205
You mean...

372
00:21:08,289 --> 00:21:11,795
Yes... I am the one
who took the master's life.

373
00:21:12,297 --> 00:21:14,050
But...
Why?

374
00:21:14,133 --> 00:21:16,514
I could not forgive him.

375
00:21:17,097 --> 00:21:20,605
As if he had forgotten
his late wife entirely...

376
00:21:20,688 --> 00:21:24,571
The master continued his
unrestrained way of life.

377
00:21:25,949 --> 00:21:28,245
I pitied the mistress so deeply...

378
00:21:28,329 --> 00:21:30,583
That's not true.
What?

379
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:33,464
The only things that man loved were detectives...

380
00:21:33,548 --> 00:21:35,802
And his late wife... only her.

381
00:21:36,135 --> 00:21:39,685
It seems he married me
to heal his grief, but...

382
00:21:39,977 --> 00:21:43,568
In the end, I could never
fill that void.

383
00:21:43,651 --> 00:21:46,615
Although, I only realized that recently.

384
00:21:47,199 --> 00:21:50,122
So that's why you took off
your wedding ring?

385
00:21:51,249 --> 00:21:54,005
It was meant as a small protest.

386
00:21:54,088 --> 00:21:57,387
That man... he never even noticed.

387
00:21:59,015 --> 00:22:00,435
I see...

388
00:22:00,810 --> 00:22:04,191
In that case, the master also,
regarding the mistress...

389
00:22:06,864 --> 00:22:12,876
♪~

390
00:23:20,720 --> 00:23:26,482
~♪

391
00:23:27,650 --> 00:23:32,034
...So, this is the prize
Kataoka-san had prepared?

392
00:23:32,452 --> 00:23:35,541
Hmph... Going and making something like this.

393
00:23:35,625 --> 00:23:37,504
He really was a colossal fool.

394
00:23:38,589 --> 00:23:43,014
I just... genuinely enjoyed
competing against him.

395
00:23:43,599 --> 00:23:45,227
Dad...

396
00:23:45,937 --> 00:23:47,398
...And?

397
00:23:49,109 --> 00:23:51,155
So what do we do with this?

398
00:23:52,826 --> 00:23:55,706
(Matsunosuke chirps)
Hey, don't tell me...

399
00:23:56,583 --> 00:23:57,627
Conan-kun?

400
00:23:58,462 --> 00:24:00,925
Ah!
Kyaa!

401
00:24:01,259 --> 00:24:03,681
So I told you, when I came to get Conan's clothes...

402
00:24:03,764 --> 00:24:05,810
Matsunosuke was sleeping in there!

403
00:24:05,893 --> 00:24:06,895
Ha...

404
00:24:07,229 --> 00:24:09,484
Everyone was mistaken.

405
00:24:09,568 --> 00:24:12,615
The witnesses... and even the culprit.

406
00:24:12,699 --> 00:24:16,331
I see... So that's how it is.

407
00:24:16,446 --> 00:24:17,946
Next Conan,

408
00:24:17,946 --> 00:24:19,946
"Promenade"

409
00:24:37,446 --> 00:24:39,746
Next Conan's Hint:

410
00:24:39,746 --> 00:24:42,046
"Walking the dog"

411
00:24:42,267 --> 00:24:43,310
Hey, let's get a dog.

412
00:24:43,394 --> 00:24:44,563
Dad's more than enough
for a watchdog.

413
00:24:44,646 --> 00:24:45,648
Arf! Woof!

414
00:24:45,731 --> 00:24:47,110
Good boy.
House.
